The paper discusses resilience in computational systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). However, the paper also discusses the dynamic interplay between the behaviors of a system and its environment, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes definitions for measures of risk and optimal design, which are topics that are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
